Legislative Document No. 418
H.P. 272 House of Representatives, February 4, 2025
An Act to Remand Individuals with Pending State Probation
Violations to the Department of Corrections Following Initial
Proceedings
Reference to the Committee on Judiciary suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative MCINTYRE of Lowell.
Cosponsored by Senator CYRWAY of Kennebec.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 17-A MRSA ยง1811, sub-ยง5-A is enacted to read:
3 5-A. Custody to Department of Corrections. If a person is denied bail under
4 subsection 5, cannot make bail set under subsection 5 or has other matters pending before
5 the court for which the person is incarcerated and bail has not yet been set, the person must
6 be remanded to the custody of the Department of Corrections until the person's pending
7 court proceedings or final disposition on the matters for which the person is incarcerated
8 has occurred.
9 SUMMARY
1100 This bill requires that, if a person who is charged with a probation violation is denied
1111 bail at the person's initial appearance for the violation, cannot make bail or has other matters
1122 for which the person is incarcerated and bail has not yet been set, the person must be
1133 remanded to the custody of the Department of Corrections until the person's pending court
1144 proceedings or final disposition on the matters for which the person is incarcerated has
1155 occurred.
